{%- comment -%}
  Vertex AI Recommendations — shared card partial.

  J11 S19/S20 (bd 2i8b.72, web-team 2026-06-11): the bespoke vrec card is gone.
  Every rec slot now renders the THEME-NATIVE product card (product-grid-item)
  inside a thin .vrec-card--standard wrapper — the generated CSS already strips
  the wrapper's container styles for exactly this pattern, so the native card's
  typography, star badge, price weight, Quick Buy icon and spacing drive the
  visual. This is the definitive fix for the recurring "rec cards don't match
  the other sliders" feedback (J10 S13, J11 S19/S20): one card template
  everywhere = parity by construction.

  The wrapper keeps:
  - .vrec-card                → rail sizing (grid-auto-columns) + nav step width
  - data-vertex-product-id    → Vertex analytics hooks
  - role="listitem"           → the rail's role="list"

  Arguments:
    product   {Product}  required — the product to render
    placement {String}   optional — unused here; kept for callsite stability
{%- endcomment -%}
<div class="vrec-card vrec-card--standard{% unless product.available %} vrec-card--sold-out{% endunless %}"
     data-vertex-product-id="{{ product.id }}"
     role="listitem">
  {% render 'product-grid-item', product: product %}
</div>
